text: DeKalb County is a county located in the state of Illinois. As of the 2020 census, the population was 100,420. Its county seat is Sycamore. DeKalb County is part of the Chicago-Naperville-Elgin, IL-IN-WI Metropolitan Statistical Area. ==References== Category:Illinois counties Category:1830s establishments in Illinois Category:1837 establishments in the United States
